{"id": "EUVD-2025-13980", "enisaUuid": "34a98160-d9de-3f01-ab78-245d70cf2794", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nusb: typec: class: Fix NULL pointer access\n\nConcurrent calls to typec_partner_unlink_device can lead to a NULL pointer\ndereference. This patch adds a mutex to protect USB device pointers and\nprevent this issue. The same mutex protects both the device pointers and\nthe partner device registration.", "datePublished": "2025-05-08T09:30:24", "dateUpdated": "2025-11-13T00:30:16", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-37809", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/1fdde62411fe65640e69bc55ea027d5b7b2f0093", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/de7c24febd21413ea8f49f61b36338b676c02852", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/ec27386de23a511008c53aa2f3434ad180a3ca9a"], "aliases": ["CVE-2025-37809", "GHSA-pfmc-fx47-cpg8"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.01, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "0cd18144-06dc-3c3c-8fe9-11a0a6d02ff5", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.15-rc4"}, {"id": "46d3bd15-0af3-39ed-8e20-211f422b289a", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "5a9e269c-92bc-308b-b2cb-e4f5fa19ca17", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "59de2a56d127890cc610f3896d5fc31887c54ac2 <ec27386de23a511008c53aa2f3434ad180a3ca9a"}, {"id": "757f8d26-2f9d-3159-bbc7-e68e27790033", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "59de2a56d127890cc610f3896d5fc31887c54ac2 <1fdde62411fe65640e69bc55ea027d5b7b2f0093"}, {"id": "8d6f8f9e-6734-3557-a352-e858ab8da2e2", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "59de2a56d127890cc610f3896d5fc31887c54ac2 <de7c24febd21413ea8f49f61b36338b676c02852"}, {"id": "b32e6a7a-2c37-3eea-a771-d80e3f4838a5", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6.7"}, {"id": "ced38e58-d71c-3c58-8f6f-acbce3a75a56", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.14.5"}, {"id": "f540b6d4-1373-36a0-835a-6c27fbd